Clearly not. The creature merely hissed and tried to charge straight at Thassalin. Fortunately, despite its size, it was agile enough to dodge, but Nyssi couldn't help but scream when she almost lost her grip on its too smooth scales.
"HOW DO YOU KILL THEM?", screamed Nyssi.
"AIM FOR THEIR HEADS!"
"THIS ISN'T GOING TO BE EASY!"
Thassalin exhaled, then circled around to get closer to the mountain he called his home. The black beast followed him, somewhat panicked when a flash of fire struck her from behind. The creature had not noticed that she was no longer alone. Her panic grew when Thassalin slowed down, then violently struck her head with his tail, causing her to veer off course.
Growling and hissing, the creature gained altitude and spat into the air. Suddenly, everything turned black, as if the monster was sucking in the light of the sky and replacing it with a perpetual cloud of night.
With no visibility left, Thassalin tried to retreat, but skimmed the tops of the trees before crashing into the clearing. As if she had known exactly where he had fallen, the creature charged straight at him, dragging the dark cloud in her wake.
"Kayel!" exclaimed Tenuk as he emerged from the cloud and began flying in circles to try to spot Nyssi and Thassalin below, in the darkness. "What do we do, Kayel? Kayel...? Kayel, where are you?"
Down below, Nyssi got up as best she could. She was sure she had broken something, but her strange, unnatural healing powers had already started taking effect. The same couldn't be said for Thassalin, who was lying on a mound, leaning against the only tree that hadn't bent under his weight. Nyssi did her best to try and reach Thassalin, but she couldn't see more than two meters ahead of her. Everything was plunged into darkness, swallowed by the impious shadows. And within those shadows, something was screaming.
An horrible club-like tail comes crashing down beside Nyssi, knocking her off her feet. She noticed, however, that the tail was swishing around, not aiming at her. The creature, from the little Nyssi could see and hear, was growling and clawing at the shadows it had created. Something was teleporting through the darkness, striking the monster and disorienting it.
A gunshot suddenly rang out, and the monster collapsed silently, lifeless. The darkness surrounding them dissipated, revealing what had happened. Standing on the creature was Kayel, gun in hand and breathing heavily.
"It's... the weirdest shadow jump I've ever done... Thanto kat'olon...", gasped Kayel. His eyes shone with a dark glow, and a dark energy coursed through his body. However, as he spoke, Kayel's organic plating regained its color, and his eyes returned to their normal yellow hue.
It took Nyssi a moment to understand what had happened. They all knew that Kayel possessed strange shadow powers. He rarely used them, as most people considered them impious and rather terrifying. But Nyssi didn't know that Kayel could use these powers in the dark. And, judging by his behavior, Kayel seemed surprised himself.
"Are you all right?" Nyssi couldn't help but ask.
"Yes, I'm fine. I killed something. It'll be better in a minute." Kayel examined his work as Tenuk made his way to land beside him, returning to his normal Spast form.
Now that the creature was no longer moving, they could better see what it was. Its skin was black as coal and slimy, but the saliva continued to adhere to its body. It had four wings and four limbs, all ending in long claws, and two straight horns protruded from its skull.
Before Tenuk and Kayel could ask what that thing was, something screamed and lunged from a nearby bush. However, the beast didn't have time to reach them, as a familiar vehicle crashed into its side, throwing it at Nyssi's feet. Taking no chances, she grabbed her gun and immediately shot it in the head, killing the creature instantly.
"Oops...", muttered Retvik from the driver's seat, before clumsily cutting the engine and jumping out of the truck. "I, uh, didn't mean to do that. Are you all right?"
"You practically missed all the action," regretted Tenuk. "Where were you?"
"You all left me. I came here as fast as I could," sighed Retvik. "May I ask what those vile things are?"
Fortunately, Retvik's question received an answer from Thassalin, who had just gotten up. He was all cut up and scratched everywhere and seemed a bit disoriented, but he didn't look too badly hurt.
"YOU KILLED THE CORRUPTED! THE INFECTED MONSTERS. CREATURES LEFT HERE WHEN THE CORRUPTION ATTACKED YOUR GODS."
"you mean... the horrible god monster that we... helped kill?" stuttered Tenuk.
"YES. ABSOLUTELY. THERE MAY BE OTHERS, BUT I DIDN'T MANAGE TO AIM FOR THEIR HEADS. I'M MISSING A GUN. PLUS, TWO AGAINST ONE ISN'T FAIR, IS IT?" Thassalin headed toward Kayel and patted his head. "THANK YOU, LITTLE ONE. YOU REMIND ME OF MY OLD FRIEND ARKADIN. JUST LESS MURDEROUS AND LESS CAPABLE OF KILLING UNIVERSES."
"Uh... thanks... I guess," said Kayel with a shrug. "So, are we done here?"
Nyssi shrugged, then grabbed her camera to photograph the beasts now definitely dead. She then took out her favorite dagger, the one of the god of death, and began cutting off one of the creature's horns before moving on to the other. But as she finished, the creatures caught fire and quickly turned into piles of ashes. The same thing happened to the horns that Nyssi had cut off.
"Well... it's both convenient and not convenient at all," she sighed. "At least, I still have the photos..."
